snippet.textDisplay:
I have been reading many comments of people saying that Coke Studio should leave the legendary songs & ghazals alone. I, myself am very sensitive about the old classics & I feel like I am cheating on them by giving a hearing to the renditions, but that resistance is only within us. 

I do agree that there are many hit & misses in the process. However, some of them are quite good. This one for instance is beautiful singing by Ali Sethi. Gave me goosebumps on some parts. We cannot ignore the good singing, great instrumentals & amazing effort by Coke Studio due to our possessiveness for the classics. 

I think it is our association with the old classics, that we do not want anything to remotely take its place. What we should consider is that today's renditions become tomorrow's favourites. Having a liking for a rendition doesn't mean discrediting the original master piece. It's more like listening to a respectful tribute being paid to the original, & can be equally cherished.
